You can search for libraries of ready4 modules using tools from the ready4 R package. <br/><br/>

<div class="highlight">

<pre class='chroma'><code class='language-r' data-lang='r'><span><span class='kr'><a href='https://rdrr.io/r/base/library.html'>library</a></span><span class='o'>(</span><span class='nv'><a href='https://ready4-dev.github.io/ready4/'>ready4</a></span><span class='o'>)</span></span></code></pre>

</div>

<br/><br/> To create the most up to date summary table of libraries of ready4 modules, you can use the `make_libraries_tb` function. <br/><br/>

<div class="highlight">

<pre class='chroma'><code class='language-r' data-lang='r'><span><span class='nv'>libraries_tb</span> <span class='o'>&lt;-</span>  <span class='nf'><a href='https://ready4-dev.github.io/ready4/reference/make_libraries_tb.html'>make_libraries_tb</a></span><span class='o'>(</span><span class='s'>"modules"</span><span class='o'>)</span></span></code></pre>

</div>

<br/><br/> Because the `make_libraries_tb` function is generated by scraping multiple ready4 R package websites, it can be a little slow to execute. A slightly faster alternative is the `get_libraries_tb` function, that downloads a pre-made and periodically updated (and therefore potentially dated) table. <br/><br/>

<div class="highlight">

<pre class='chroma'><code class='language-r' data-lang='r'><span><span class='c'># Not run</span></span>
<span><span class='c'># libraries_tb &lt;- get_libraries_tb()</span></span></code></pre>

</div>

<br/><br/> Whichever method you use to generate the table, you can format the table for HTML output using the `print_packages` function. <br/><br/>

<div class="highlight">

<pre class='chroma'><code class='language-r' data-lang='r'><span><span class='nf'><a href='https://ready4-dev.github.io/ready4/reference/print_packages.html'>print_packages</a></span><span class='o'>(</span><span class='nv'>libraries_tb</span>,</span>
<span>               include_1L_chr <span class='o'>=</span> <span class='s'>"modules"</span><span class='o'>)</span></span></code></pre>

</div>

<br/><br/>
